(492, 124, 'REB Permission Issue', 'muhitur.rahman@summitcommunications.net,ahsanur.rab@summitcommunications.net', '2016-09-19 18:38:55', '2016-10-03 18:39:17', 'active', 'The CMO instructed HoD Planning to come up with an alternative strategy regarding network expansion plan with REB, considering REB’s defensive attitude due to several recent issues such as Transformer theft, fatalities, increase in maintenance cost and sharing of pole construction cost. \r\nmuhitur.rahman : we Cannot expand our network without using REB Poles. If we want to avoid REB Poles than we need to focus on UG Network expansion, which is time consuming and expansive. Other way to expand OH network is to install own Poles. We should Approach REB on a partnership modality which might attract REB, for example creating and providing One LAN nationwide for usage in REB office using SCL infrastructure for free\r\n\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '80-100', 492),
